text: The Five Poisons (Chinese: 五毒; Pinyin: wǔ dú; Jyutping: ng5 duk6; Vietnamese: Ngũ độc) can refer to: *An ancient Chinese set of poisonous/hazardous animals, they are: Snakes. Scorpions. Centipedes. Toads. Spiders. *Five threats that the Chinese Communist Party sees for its rule over Mainland China. ==References== category:history of China
title: Five Poisons
